    "comment": "Rationale: This study uses two methods to describe the subcellular localization of RIM4gamma.\n\n-Using subcellular fractionation based on synaptosomes, RIM4gamma was detected in a triton-insoluble fraction. This fraction is enriched in pre-and postsynaptic densities. (Figure 2A).\n-In confocal microscopy, RIM4gamma was present in dendrites, with some overlap with the synaptic markers synapsin and PSD95 (figure 2C-E).\n\nNeither experiment has sufficient resolution to discriminate between pre- and postsynaptic localization.\n\nThe antibody used was verified using RNA knockdown and western blot analysis (Figure 3A).. Experimental description: The studies were performed on brains of Wistar rats of either sex (Charles River).",
